no-tabs.description:
Description

This rule looks for tabs anywhere inside a file: code, comments or anything else.

Examples ofincorrectcode for this rule:

/* eslint no-tabs: "error" */

var a 	= 2;

/**
* 		 it's a test function
*/
function test(){}

var x = 1; // 	 test

Examples ofcorrectcode for this rule:

/* eslint no-tabs: "error" */

var a = 2;

/**
* it's a test function
*/
function test(){}

var x = 1; // test

Options

This rule has an optional object option with the following properties:

- allowIndentationTabs(default: false): If this is set to true, then the rule will not report tabs used for indentation.

allowIndentationTabs

Examples ofcorrectcode for this rule with theallowIndentationTabs: trueoption:

/* eslint no-tabs: ["error", { allowIndentationTabs: true }] */

function test() {
	doSomething();
}

	// comment with leading indentation tab
